-- Mexican Authorities Say Armed Men Abduct 22 in Acapulco, Reforma Reports
-- B y   T h o m a s   B l a c k
-- 2010-10-02T19:23:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-02/mexican-authorities-say-armed-men-abduct-22-in-acapulco-reforma-reports.html
Mexican authorities said a group of
22 people were abducted in the beach resort city of Acapulco by
armed men, Reforma newspaper reported today on its Web site.  The attorney general’s office for the state of Guerrero
said the group was traveling from the state of Michoacan in four
vehicles when they were taken by force on Sept. 30, Reforma
reported. Authorities said they don’t know the motive of the
abduction or the whereabouts of the group.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Thomas Black  in Monterrey at 
